    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "9ec57777990542dc",
      "text": "# Cross-domain\n[[OIDC Credential Provider]], a new spec at the OpenID Foundation, is challenging the notion that the identity that a user receives has to be an identity entirely bound to its domain. It offers traditional IdPs a way to issue credentials that are portable and can cross domains because the identity/identifier is no longer coupled to the provider as is the case with an identity token.\n"
    },
    {
